Steps to Set Up CI/CD for Static Web App Using Jenkins, Docker, and Ansible
1. Prepare Jenkins Server

Install Jenkins on your server (Master).

Install necessary plugins:

Git

Pipeline

Ansible (optional, if you want to run playbooks from Jenkins)

Ensure Jenkins user can run Docker commands:

Add Jenkins to Docker group:

sudo usermod -aG docker jenkins

Restart Jenkins or logout/login.

Enable passwordless sudo for Jenkins if needed:

jenkins ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD:ALL
2. Prepare Worker Node

Install Docker on worker node.

Create a user ansible (or any non-root user for SSH):

sudo adduser ansible

Add ansible user to Docker group:

sudo usermod -aG docker ansible

Enable passwordless sudo for ansible user:

ansible ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD:ALL
3. SSH Key Setup

On Jenkins server, generate SSH keys (if not present):

ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "jenkins@server"

Copy public key to worker node:

ssh-copy-id -i ~/.ssh/id_ed25519 ansible@<worker-ip>

Test SSH access:

ssh -i ~/.ssh/id_ed25519 ansible@<worker-ip>
4. Docker Hub Setup

Create a Docker Hub account.

Create a repository (e.g., static-web).

Test Docker login from Jenkins:

docker login -u <docker-username>
5. GitHub Repository

Create a GitHub repository for your project (e.g., project-repo).

Add your static web app files (HTML, CSS, JS) and Dockerfile.

Dockerfile Example:

FROM nginx:latest
COPY src/ /usr/share/nginx/html
EXPOSE 80
6. Jenkins Pipeline

Create a Jenkins pipeline job.

Set SCM to your GitHub repository.

Use a Jenkinsfile like:

pipeline {
    agent any
    environment { ANSIBLE_HOST_KEY_CHECKING = 'False' }
    stages {
        stage('Clone Repo') {
            steps { git branch: 'main', url: 'https://github.com/<github-username>/project-repo.git' }
        }
        stage('Build Docker Image') {
            steps { sh 'docker build -t <docker-username>/static-web .' }
        }
        stage('Docker Login') {
            steps { sh 'docker login -u <docker-username>' }
        }
        stage('Push Image') {
            steps { sh 'docker push <docker-username>/static-web' }
        }
        stage('Deploy using Ansible') {
            steps { sh 'ansible-playbook -i inventory playbook.yml' }
        }
    }
}
7. Ansible Setup

Create an inventory file:

[dev]
<worker-ip> ansible_user=ansible ansible_ssh_private_key_file=/var/lib/jenkins/.ssh/id_ed25519

Create playbook.yml to deploy Docker container:

- name: docker operation using jenkins
  hosts: dev
  user: ansible
  become: true
  connection: ssh

  tasks:
    - name: Pull latest image
      command: docker pull <docker-username>/static-web

    - name: Stop existing container
      command: docker rm -f webapp
      ignore_errors: yes

    - name: Run container
      command: docker run -d -p 8085:80 --name webapp <docker-username>/static-web
8. Testing the Pipeline

Trigger the Jenkins pipeline.

Jenkins stages:

Clone repo

Build Docker image

Login & Push to Docker Hub

Run Ansible playbook on worker node

Check the web app in browser:

http://<worker-ip>:8085

✅ Important Notes

Make sure Docker is running on both Jenkins and worker nodes.

Make sure SSH keys are correct and accessible by Jenkins.

Do not hardcode your personal usernames or passwords in the Jenkinsfile; use environment variables if possible.

Test each stage separately before running full pipeline.
